  "collections_page_mount_all": "Mount all",
  "collections_page_intro_1": "The first hour of a sprint is not for coding. It is for triage: sifting through the weekend's pull requests, the overnight on-call alerts, and the half-finished thought a colleague left in Slack at eleven on Friday. What follows is the set of skills that makes that hour tolerable.",
  "collections_page_intro_2": "Each skill has earned its spot by surviving contact with a real queue and a reviewer who does not tolerate nits. They are ordered not by popularity, but by the order in which I reach for them.",
